		<td><b>What appears on the wires when you write or read from $4016?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Referring to the controller port...
<br />What signal appears on the wires when you write a zero in the least significant bit to $4016?  For a 1 in the least significant bit, I think it's a double width pulse, and for a read of $4016, I think it's a single width pulse.  Does anything appear on the wire when you write a zero?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>blargg</b> [ Sat Feb 07, 2009 8:12 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />What you write to $4016 is latched and output continuously on the strobe line. When you read from $4016, you get the inverted state of the data line (+5V=0 GND=1), and the clock line is pulsed. The clock line is normally high, low momentarily when pulsed.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
